TY - JOUR T1 - Some Urgent Issues of Georgia’s Geography AU - Nodar Elizbarashvili AU - Giorgi Meladze AU - Maia Meladze AU - David Svanadze AU - Lizi Gadrani AU - Josef Lazarashvili Y1 - 2015/07/02 PY - 2015 N1 - https://doi.org/10.11648/j.earth.s.2015040501.11 DO - 10.11648/j.earth.s.2015040501.11 T2 - Earth Sciences JF - Earth Sciences JO - Earth Sciences SP - 1 EP - 7 PB - Science Publishing Group SN - 2328-5982 UR - https://doi.org/10.11648/j.earth.s.2015040501.11 AB - Geography is facing new challenges in Georgia. On the one hand, it is related to evaluation of current condition of the country and its geo-ecological issues, and on the other hand, the requirements of practice and the prospects of socio-economic development. The requirements of practice imply several urgent issues such as new orientation of the land use and the optimal use of the region's natural-resource potential, demographic stability and development of mountainous areas. The prospects of the country’s development include the urgent issues such as global environmental problems and prediction of geo-system conditions, development of military geography and planning of environmentally strained areas. In order to present and solve these problems effectively, Georgian School of Geography should play a key role, which will become a prerequisite for its further development. VL - 4 IS - 5-1 ER -

